    {
        ".     Ebbinghaus made several findings that are still relevant and supported to this day. First, Ebbinghaus made a 2,300 three letter syllables to measure mental associations that helped him find that memory is orderly. Second, and arguably his most famous finding, was the ": null
    },
    {
